  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Cut the <strong>potatoes</strong> (skins on) into wedges</p><p>Chop the <strong>leek<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> in half lengthways, wash thoroughly to remove any grit then top and tail</p><p>Slice <strong>half </strong>the <strong>leek </strong>finely and chop the <strong>remaining leek </strong>into 4 <span class=\"text-danger\">[8] </span>pieces</p><p>Chop the <strong>parsley & dill </strong>finely, including the stalks</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1668523771832-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1668523771832-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1668523771832-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1668523771832-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1668523771832-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>wedges </strong>to a baking tray with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil </strong>and a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up and put the tray in the oven for an initial 15 min or until the wedges are beginning to brown</p><p>Chop the <strong>smoked basa fillets</strong> into small, bite-sized pieces</p><p>Grate the <strong>cheddar cheese </strong>finely</p><p>Wash the <strong>spinach</strong> and pat it dry with kitchen paper</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1668523775003-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1668523775003-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1668523775003-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1668523775003-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1668523775003-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) over a medium heat with 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp] </span><strong>olive oil</strong></p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>sliced leek </strong>with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for 3-4 min until softened</p><p>Once softened, add 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span> <strong>flour</strong> and stir with a wooden spoon for 1-2 min or until a sandy paste coats the leek – this is your <strong>leek roux</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1668523778519-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1668523778519-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1668523778519-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1668523778519-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1668523778519-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Gradually whisk 100ml<span class=\"text-danger\"> [200ml] </span><strong>milk</strong> into the <strong>leek roux</strong>, a little at a time, and cook for 3-4 min or until a smooth, thick sauce remains</p><p>Once thickened, add the <strong>chopped smoked basa</strong>, <strong>chopped parsley & dill</strong>, <strong>half </strong>the <strong>grated cheese </strong>(you'll use the rest later!), a generous grind of <strong>black pepper</strong> and stir until the cheese has melted – this is your <strong>pasty filling</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1668523782629-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1668523782629-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1668523782629-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1668523782629-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1668523782629-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Dust a work surface with a small handful of <strong>flour</strong></p><p>Unwrap the <strong>puff pastry </strong>and roll it out to approx. 0.5cm thickness with a <strong>rolling pin</strong></p><p>Cut the <strong>puff pastry</strong> into 2<span class=\"text-danger\"> [4]<strong> </span></strong>rectangles and add them to a<strong> baking paper</strong>-lined<strong> </strong>baking tray</p><p>Tip: Cooking for 4? Use 2 trays!</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1668523786342-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1668523786342-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1668523786342-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1668523786342-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1668523786342-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Divide the <strong>pasty filling</strong> between the <strong>pastry rectangles</strong>, covering only one half and brush a little <strong>cold water</strong> around the edges of the pastry (this helps to seal the pastry!)</p><p>Fold the <strong>pastry</strong> over the filling and seal firmly together then use a fork to crimp along the join and prick an air hole in the centre of each sealed pastry rectangle</p><p>Top with the <strong>remaining grated cheese</strong>, then put the tray in the oven for 17-20 min or until golden and cooked through – these are your <strong>cheesy leek & smoked basa pasties</strong></p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1668523791795-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1668523791795-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1668523791795-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1668523791795-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1668523791795-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the wedges have had an initial 15 min, remove the tray from the oven and add the <strong>leek pieces </strong>with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong></p><p>Return the tray to the oven for a further 10 min or until the leek has softened and the wedges are golden and crisp</p><p>Once the leek has softened, remove the tray from the oven and top the leek with the <strong>spinach</strong> and return it to the oven for a final 1-2 min or until wilted – this is your <strong>roasted leek & spinach</strong></p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1668523796017-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1668523796017-x400.jpg",
